article.headline: Radford 69, Western Carolina 56
article.story: BLACKSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Chris Oliver had 29 points as Radford defeated Western Carolina 69-56 on Saturday in the NABC Classic. White Holcomb-Faye added 18 for Radford (1-1), and Reggie McIntyre had 12 points. Western Carolina (1-1) jumped took an early 6-2 lead, but the Highlanders came storming back, including a 14-2 run that helped put them ahead 29-18 at the half. The Catamounts cut the lead to four at 31-27 early in the second half on Eric Wilson's 3-pointer before Radford took off again, including a 12-0 run. Antonio Russell finished with 12 points for Western Carolina, and Charles Bouie had 10.
